      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, especially when the top ones look fine, is a classic sign of a few things, most likely a nutrient deficiency or a watering issue. It's often related to mobile nutrients, like nitrogen, which the plant moves from older leaves to support new growth at the top. Try checking your soil moisture levels first; if they're consistently too dry or too soggy, that could be the culprit. A good soil test would tell you exactly what your plants are craving.",
