      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you suspect a nitrogen issue, you can definitely boost the soil with a nitrogen-rich fertilizer, like one containing ammonium nitrate or blood meal. You might want to apply a slow-release granular fertilizer around the base of the plants, following the package directions carefully. Don't overdo it, though, because too much fertilizer can burn the roots, and you don't need to make a big, sudden change to the soil pH unless your soil test specifically called for it. A balanced feeding schedule is usually the best approach for tomatoes.",
