    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. i'll try the blood meal. i'm just worried that something is actually stealing the nutrients before the plants can even use them, like if the soil is just drained or something. any way to prevent that kind of depletion?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That worry about nutrient theft is very real, and it's often related to drainage or soil structure. If your soil drains too quickly, it can leach out valuable nutrients, which is like a sneaky, fast-moving thief of fertilizer. To prevent this, you can incorporate plenty of organic matter, like compost, into your soil. Compost acts like a sponge, holding onto those vital nutrients so the roots can access them slowly and steadily. This builds better soil structure overall.",
      "source": "target",
